The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Johannesburg, June 20: South African telecom giant MTN, which is in exclusive talks with Anil Ambani led Reliance Communications for a possible alliance, today said its shareholders had approved all resolutions at its annual general meeting including buyback of up to 10 per cent of the shares.                             
	 New Delhi, June 20: Japan has agreed to allot 20 additional slots for Indian carriers at Narita International Airport by 2010, which will facilitate operation of up to 28 flights to Tokyo every week from four at present.                            
	 New Delhi, June 20: The on-going fight between Sun Pharma and Taro Pharmaceuticals has reached court with the Israeli firm filing two law suits against the Indian firm, weeks after their $454 million-merger deal fell apart.
                                                                                                                         
